.TH OPENTELEMETRY-JAVA 1 "@DATE@" "opentelemetry-java-autoinstrumentation @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
opentelemetry-java \- OpenTelemetry Java Auto-Instrumentation Agent
.SH SYNOPSIS
The Java agent is loaded automatically by the OpenTelemetry Injector when a
Java application starts. Manual usage:
.PP
.B java -javaagent:/usr/lib/opentelemetry/java/opentelemetry-javaagent.jar
.I [options]
.B -jar myapp.jar
.SH DESCRIPTION
The OpenTelemetry Java Auto-Instrumentation Agent automatically instruments
Java applications to collect distributed traces, metrics, and logs without
requiring code changes.
.PP
When used with the OpenTelemetry Injector package, the agent is automatically
attached to all Java processes.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /usr/lib/opentelemetry/java/opentelemetry-javaagent.jar
The Java agent JAR file.
.TP
.B /etc/opentelemetry/java/otel-config.yaml
Optional declarative configuration file.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B OTEL_SERVICE_NAME
Set the service name for telemetry data.
.TP
.B OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT
Set the OTLP exporter endpoint (e.g., http://localhost:4317).
.TP
.B OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER
Set the traces exporter (otlp, console, none). Default: otlp
.TP
.B OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER
Set the metrics exporter (otlp, console, none). Default: otlp
.TP
.B OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER
Set the logs exporter (otlp, console, none). Default: otlp
.TP
.B OTEL_JAVAAGENT_ENABLED
Set to "false" to disable the agent. Default: true
.TP
.B OTEL_EXPERIMENTAL_CONFIG_FILE
Path to a declarative configuration file.
.SH EXAMPLES
Manually run a Java application with the agent:
.PP
.RS
java -javaagent:/usr/lib/opentelemetry/java/opentelemetry-javaagent.jar \\
  -Dotel.service.name=myapp \\
  -jar myapp.jar
.RE
